Announcing the cover model *drum roll*
.
.
 @arely.handling and Tone’s 58. I always struggle picking the cover because I don’t want just anybody being the face of the calendar. This year was easy though after working with Arely in the past. We shot for La Vuelta’s calendar last year and got some badass pictures. She also came out in Beto’s Centerfoldz magazine. She’s big in the street racing scene so it was time to bring her over to the lowriders. Arely also has a dealership and her own car wrapping business. So hit her up if you need any of that.

With the year coming to an end, I want to thank everyone for their support. All the likes, shares, comments and sales have been noticed and they go a long way. Huge shoutout to the car owners and models who helped me create some badass images. I have new plans with Twisted Fate the coming year. More info on a post tomorrow. I’m also doing a year end closeout. All the products on my shop are on sale. Trying to make room for more merch. They will go back to regular price on the 7th. 
I hope y’all had a good year and the next one is even better.

Happy New Year!! 
.
As mentioned before, there is going to be changes to Twisted Fate. I’m going to be posting all types of content. 
.
I’m not going to stop shooting lowriders and models, never will, but I need to push my creativity and expand my skills in different fields. I want to explore new editing styles, new subjects and hopefully bring in a bigger audience. 
.
I hardly reach 10% of my followers so I doubt this matters either way.

Another goal of mine is to do more video. It’s a whole different beast but I like the story telling aspect. I don’t want to make those cringy reels, I want to tell a story. Might have to make cringe reels to get more exposure though so don’t get mad hahaha.

This is an actual 727 airplane. The owner gutted it and turned it into a home. Now he lives in the middle of nowhere. He said he is running a fundraiser to buy another plane in Japan and also turn it into a home. Who’s heard of him?
